thread.title: Westpac delays two Pac Island bank sales
thread.title_full: Westpac delays two Pac Island bank sales

author: news.com.au
title: Westpac delays two Pac Island bank sales
text:
WESTPAC has delayed plans to sell its operations in Vanuatu and the Solomon Islands due to central bank intervention.
DUE to the devastating impact of Cyclone Pam in March, the Reserve Bank of Vanuatu has decided now is not the time for a change of control in the country's banking sector.
Westpac's planned sale of its Solomon Islands operations has also failed to receive full approval from the Central Bank of Solomon Islands. The banking giant announced in January it would sell its businesses in five Pacific Island nations to the Bank of South Pacific for $125 million. The sale of Westpac's operations in the Cook Islands, Samoa and Tonga has been finalised in a $91 million deal, and consultation with the Central Bank of Solomon Islands will continue in order to obtain all necessary approvals, Westpac said. "Westpac will continue to support Vanuatu through its recovery process, and it will be business as usual for our customers and employees," it said. The bank's sale of its Pacific Island operations will not have a material impact on its financial position, it said.
